This is the README file the CGAL Kernel library

  

See in the INSTALL file for how to install CGAL

See directory doc_ps for some Postscript documents, among others the 
Cgal Reference Manual.

See directory doc_html for the online manual cgal.html.

Please have a look at README_RTTI if you are using g++

The directory 'example' is intended for the first steps with Cgal.
Users should copy it to their own file system, read the README to
see how to adapt the makefile, compile the two example programs
and use them as a starting point for developing Cgal code.

CGAl-0.5/makefile is a master copy of a makefile for users of Cgal.

